This function acts as a hook before data persists. It allows us to safely transfer a stored original value to a new attribute name to preserve history.

```python
def pre_save(self, model_instance, add):
        """Save the original_value."""
        if self.original:
            original_value = getattr(model_instance, self.original)
            setattr(model_instance, self.attname, original_value)

        return super(HashMixin, self).pre_save(model_instance, add)
```

By checking `self.original`, the code first retrieves the value from the source attribute and then sets it using the target name (`self.attname`). This ensures that even if a model instance undergoes transformation before saving.
